  <exercise>
    <title>Question 4</title>
    <p>
      For each of the following curves, convert the equation from rectangular to polar coordinates and sketch it.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          <m>y^2 + (x - 1)^2 = 1</m>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <m>y=3</m>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <alert>(H)</alert> <m>9xy = 2</m>
        </p>
        <solution>
          <p>
            We have
            <md>
              <mrow>9xy \amp = 9r^2\cos(\theta)\sin(\theta)</mrow>
              <mrow>\amp =\frac{9}{2}r^2\text{sin}(2\theta) = 2 </mrow>
            </md>
            Rearranging, 
            <me> \implies r = \frac{2}{3\sqrt{\sin(2\theta)}}.</me>
            
          </p>
          <interactive desmos="gi8bp68vj2" width="60%" aspect="2:3" />
        </solution>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <alert>(H)</alert> <m>(x^2 + y^2 + 3x)^2 = 9(x^2 + y^2)</m>
        </p>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <me>(r^2 + 3x)^2 = 9r^2</me>
            <me>(r^2 + 3 r\cos(\theta))^2 = 9r^2</me>
            Taking the positive square-root and reearranging
            <me>r = 3(1 - \cos(\theta)).</me>
          </p>
          <interactive desmos="ewu7wtpszy" width="60%" aspect="2:3" />
        </solution>
      </li>
    </ol>
    
  </exercise>
  

